w us something about the visual event of seeing itself. The Phantom Image will be essential for anyone interested in ancient art, visual culture, and the history of the image.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aArt, Roman. 0aDead. 0aGhosts in art. 0aGhostszRome. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aBelief.  aFunerary art.  aGender.  aGhosts.  aPerspective.  aRepresentation.  aRoman art.  aSarcophagi.  aVision.  aVisual culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2019z9783110605747oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226648323423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226648323.jpg  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DADb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019